OL,3,CMore than 250 patients a week 'die
OL,4,Cneedlessly due to long A&E waits'
OL,6,FCalculations by the Royal College of
OL,7,FEmergency Medicine (RCEM) which have
OL,8,Fbeen shared with the PA news agency
OL,9,Fsuggest patients are coming to harm
OL,10,Fdue to spending hours in A&E,
OL,11,Fparticularly after a decision has been
OL,12,Fmade to admit them.
OL,14,FThe NHS recovery plan set a target of
OL,15,FMarch for 76% of patients attending
OL,16,FA&E to be admitted, transferred or
OL,17,Fdischarged within four hours.
OL,19,FBut data for March shows just 70.9% of
OL,20,Fpatients were seen within that time
OL,21,Fframe.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/13
