OL,3,CMore than 250 patients a week 'die
OL,4,Cneedlessly due to long A&E waits'
OL,6,FThe risk of death started to increase
OL,7,Fafter five hours and got worse with
OL,8,Flonger waiting times.
OL,10,FIn 2022, the RCEM said it believed 300
OL,11,Fto 500 excess deaths were likely to
OL,12,Fhave occurred in England each week
OL,13,Fusing this calculation, but it has
OL,14,Fsince carried out a Freedom of
OL,15,FInformation audit of NHS trusts to
OL,16,Frefine this figure.
OL,18,FThis found that 65% of people waiting
OL,19,F12 hours or more in A&E are patients
OL,20,Fwaiting for a hospital bed.
